# tasks.md completion protocol

When the user asks to implement a task from `tasks.md` (or references a task ID like “4.1”), treat updating `tasks.md` as part of the definition of done.

## When to mark complete automatically

- **Behavior/logic changes**: only mark the task complete after relevant **tests pass** (and lint/format if part of the repo workflow).
- **Styling/layout-only changes**: only mark the task complete after either:
  - the agent has **visually reviewed** light + dark mode, responsive breakpoints, and keyboard focus states

## How to mark complete

- Preserve the existing formatting/style of `tasks.md`.
- Prefer the existing convention: strike checklist bullets with `~~...~~` and add a short `> Completed:` note under the task.

## If verification can’t be done

- Do **not** mark the task complete.
- Instead, leave a short note under the task describing what is missing (e.g. failing test name, or “needs visual review confirmation”).
